<div n="apparatus"><head>Apparatus</head><p>l. 4, the last letter could be <foreign lang="grc">Ε</foreign>, and it is possible that the last two begin a second  cognomen (but if so the man is not otherwise known).</p></div><div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p><gap unit="character" dim="left" extent="unknown" reason="lost"/> the copy <supplied reason="lost">of the inscription was deposited in the property-archive in the staphanephorate</supplied> of Tib<supplied reason="abbreviation">erius</supplied> Cl<supplied reason="abbreviation">audius</supplied> Diogenes, ?month <supplied reason="lost">of</supplied><gap unit="character" dim="right" extent="unknown" reason="lost"/></p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>ll. 1, 2 seem beyond interpretation.</p><p> ll. 3, 4 can be restored with high probability as from a penal formula (so already Cormack). We offer a standard wording, but there is some variety in texts without real differences in meaning.</p>
</div>
